# Coral Kingdoms water (locked)

**Coral Kingdoms** uses `waterBodyType: 'LAKE'` but its own shallow tropical bay palette — not generic LAKE colors.

## Locked values (`src/water/waterBodyTypes.js`)

| Role | Hex |
|------|-----|
| Shallow | `#42C4FF` (bright aqua blue) |
| Deep | `#186890` |
| Fog | `#2A88B8` |

- **Helper:** `applyCoralKingdomsWaterColors(material)`
- Also clears `uFlatWater` / `uOpaqueDeep` so Fjord-style flat water never bleeds in.

## Location switch order (`main.js`)

Call **`setCoralReefEnabled` before `setWaterBodyType`** so returning to Coral Kingdoms re-applies bay colors and reef bed/caustics in one pass.

## Rules

- Do not use generic LAKE deep blue (`#004466`) at Coral Kingdoms.
- `_syncCoralKingdomsBed` must call `applyCoralKingdomsWaterColors` when reef is active.
- `setWaterBodyType('LAKE')` must call `applyCoralKingdomsWaterColors` when `_coralReefLocationEnabled` is true.
